11 "§ 90-21.163. Eligibility.
12 (a) A physician must meet the eligibility requirements as defined in G.S. 90-21.162(11)
13 to receive an expedited license under the terms and provisions of the Compact.
14 (b) A physician who does not meet the requirements of G.S. 90-21.162(11) may obtain a
15 license to practice medicine in a member state if the individual complies with all laws and
16 requirements, other than the Compact, relating to the issuance of a license to practice medicine
17 in that state.
18 "§ 90-21.164. Designation of state of principal license.
19 (a) A physician shall designate a member state as the state of principal license for
20 purposes of registration for expedited licensure through the Compact if the physician possesses
21 a full and unrestricted license to practice medicine in that state, and that state meets any one of
22 the following qualifications:
23 (1) The state is the principal residence for the physician.
24 (2) The physician conducts at least twenty-five percent (25%) of their practice of
25 medicine in the state.
26 (3) The state is the location of the physician's employer.
27 If no state qualifies under subdivision (1), (2), or (3) of this subsection, then the physician
28 may designate the state of residence for the purpose of federal income tax as their state of
29 principal license.
30 (b) A physician may redesignate a member state as a state of principal license at any time,
31 as long as the state meets the requirements of subsection (a) of this section.
32 (c) The Interstate Commission is authorized to develop rules to facilitate redesignation
33 of another member state as the state of principal license.
34 "§ 90-21.165. Application and issuance of expedited licensure.
35 (a) A physician seeking licensure through the Compact shall file an application for an
36 expedited license with the member board of the state selected by the physician as the state of
37 principal license.
38 (b) Upon receipt of an application for an expedited license, the member board within the
39 state selected as the state of principal license shall evaluate whether the physician is eligible for
40 expedited licensure and issue a letter of qualification, verifying or denying the physician's
41 eligibility, to the Interstate Commission.
42 (c) Static qualifications, which include verification of medical education, graduate
43 medical education, results of any medical or licensing examination, and other qualifications as
44 determined by the Interstate Commission through rule, shall not be subject to additional primary
45 source verification where already primary source verified by the state of principal license.
46 (d) The member board within the state selected as the state of principal license shall, in
47 the course of verifying eligibility, perform a criminal background check of an applicant,
48 including the use of the results of fingerprint or other biometric data checks in compliance with
49 the requirements of the Federal Bureau of Investigation, with the exception of federal employees
50 who have suitability determination in accordance with 5 C.F.R. § 731.202.
