20 "§ 90-21.166. Fees for expedited licensure.
21 (a) A member state issuing an expedited license authorizing the practice of medicine in
22 that state may impose a fee for a license issued or renewed through the Compact.
23 (b) The Interstate Commission is authorized to develop rules regarding fees for expedited
24 licenses.
25 "§ 90-21.167. Renewal and continued participation.
26 (a) A physician seeking to renew an expedited license granted in a member state shall
27 complete a renewal process with the Interstate Commission if the physician meets all of the
28 following qualifications:
29 (1) Maintains a full and unrestricted license in a state of principal license.
30 (2) Has not been convicted, received adjudication, deferred adjudication,
31 community supervision, or deferred disposition for any offense by a court of
32 appropriate jurisdiction.
33 (3) Has not had a license authorizing the practice of medicine subject to discipline
34 by a licensing agency in any state, federal, or foreign jurisdiction, excluding
35 any action related to nonpayment of fees related to a license.
36 (4) Has not had a controlled substance license or permit suspended or revoked by
37 a state or the United States Drug Enforcement Administration.
38 (b) Physicians shall comply with all continuing professional development or continuing
39 medical education requirements for renewal of a license issued by a member state.
40 (c) The Interstate Commission shall collect any renewal fees charged for the renewal of
41 a license and distribute the fees to the applicable member board.
42 (d) Upon receipt of any renewal fees collected under subsection (c) of this section, a
43 member board shall renew the physician's license.
44 (e) Physician information collected by the Interstate Commission during the renewal
45 process will be distributed to all member boards.
46 (f) The Interstate Commission is authorized to develop rules to address renewal of
47 licenses obtained through the Compact.
48 "§ 90-21.168. Coordinated information system.
49 (a) The Interstate Commission shall establish a database of all physicians who are
50 licensed, or who have applied for licensure, under G.S. 90-21.165.
